### 1. Naive solution using a loop:
##### When `n` is odd:
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/23e33018-fb0a-4d00-a796-b6c0b18fb1e8_1674414311.8147304.png)

##### When `n` is even:
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/3d021e25-740e-4017-aa2e-f262fbe3287a_1674414531.4001348.png)

#### Code:

``` java []
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int n) {
        int ops = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
            int x = 2 * i + 1;  // given in statement
            ops += (n - x);
        } 

        return ops;
    }
}

// TC: O(n/2) => O(n), SC: O(1)
```
---
### 2. Optimal solution (No loop):
##### When `n` is odd:
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d13fe28a-c3f3-4d2f-b461-eec7bf86465b_1674415315.432981.png)

##### When `n` is even:
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/97972aca-dd14-4638-a4b6-02525a49a4eb_1674415114.2349482.png)

#### Code:
``` java []
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int n) {
        int mid = n / 2;
        return mid * ((n % 2 == 0)? mid : (mid + 1));
    }
}

// TC: O(1), SC: O(1)
```
#### OR
``` java []
class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int n) {
        int mid = n / 2;
        return mid * (mid + n % 2);
    }
}

// TC: O(1), SC: O(1)
```

