A simple O(n) solution is to set every element to n.
Now since we can get two elements close to n at the same time ({a[0], a[n-1]}, {a[1], a[n-2]} .. {a[n/2], a[n/2]})

We just need to iterate i from 0 to n/2 and find the distance between n and 2*i + 1

Time Complexity : `O(n)`
Space Complexity : `O(1)`

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(int n) {
        int ops = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n/2; i++) {
            int curr = (2*i) + 1;
            ops += abs(n-curr);
        }
        return ops;
    }
};
```

