solutions.content:
Figuring out the general term of the series can be tricky.
The key here is to focus on the number of final operations required.

Starting with `n`=1, the first few terms of the series would be:
0, 1, 2, 4, 6, 9, 12, 16, 20, 25 and so on... 

If you see the difference between 2 consecutive terms, now you begin to see a pattern:
1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4 and so on...  

We separate the odd and even terms and get the 2 new series:
For `n%2==0` we get 1, 4, 9, 16, 25...
For `n%2==1` we get 0, 2, 6, 12, 20...

Now, it is clear that for all the even numbers, we have to return the square of `n/2` 
For odd, simply return `n/2` multiplied by the next consecutive number `n/2 +1`

Feel free to optimize further or mention any different approach of handling this problem :)
```
class Solution {
public:
