# Intuition
Intuition: the array is composed of n odd elements and no matter how much operation we perform the sum of all elements will be same because if we increase one element then we also decrease the other.

# Approach
Thus using Arthemetic Progesssion to determine the sum of n odd numbers which is n^2.
 then we distribute n^2 through the array of size n that means n^2/n which is n. 
Thus for an ideal array all element will be equal to n
  Eg:    --  arr[size:6] =1 3 5 7 9 11   sum(n^2)=6*6=36
    ---- ideal array is :   6 6 6 6 6 6
     ----    differnce is:  -5 -3 -1 1 3 5

Now all we have to do is count how many units of +ve and -ve 
will collide to yield ideal array. In above example ans is 9 (5 and -5 
collide thus 5 operation,  3 and -3 thus 3 opn, 1 and -1 thus 1 opn, and now adding them all 5+3+1=9  return 9)

Note this is for even of elements for odd no center element will be 0 eg:
      1 3 5 7 9
      5 5 5 5 5 
      -4 -2 0 2 4   ---   ans is 4+2 = 6

