# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- For odd **n**, transform every array element to the middle element in the array.
- For even **n**, transform every array element to the everage of two middle elements in the array.
- Why this works? for every element in the first half of array that gets increamented by **x**, there is a corresponding element in the second half that needs to be decreamented by **x** for it to be equal to the final value.

---



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(int n) {
        int ans=0;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i+=2)
            ans += (n - i);
        return ans;
    }
};
//TC : O(n)
```

- From this we can easily derive a mathematical formulae
- We are adding n (n/2) times
- From this subtract the sum of odd number uptill n.
- [Sum of all odd numbers uptill n](https://www.cuemath.com/algebra/sum-of-odd-numbers/) = pow((n/2),2) = (n/2)*(n/2)
- So, ans = n*(n/2) - (n/2)*(n/2)
- ans = (n*n)/4

